cafes.name: Starry Night Cat Caf√©
cafes.address: 1141 Clark St, Stevens Point, WI 54481, USA

text.text:
I brought my three kids to the Cat Caf√©, and it was such a delightful experience for all of us. My kids have always wanted a cat, and this visit gave them the perfect opportunity to interact and play with cats in a safe and fun environment. They absolutely loved spending time in both the kitten room and the adult cat room, getting a chance to cuddle and play with the cats for 45 minutes.

The chai tea I had was wonderful‚Äîrich and perfectly spiced‚Äîand the cake pops were a delicious treat that everyone enjoyed. Although visiting on the weekend was a bit pricier, I learned that weekday rates are slightly lower, which is great for planning our next visit. Overall, it was a fantastic experience for both me and my kids, and we left with smiles all around!

there are cats and the food and service is excellent
one gripe that I know some people have is needing to pay to play with the cats, but I'm sure it keeps too many people from coming in and overwhelming the cats
plus you can still watch the cats from the cafe area--as someone who's pretty allergic to cats, I appreciate this setup as I can still look at the adorable cats while not triggering my allergies
they also have a small discount for college students with ID, which is nice especially since it's fairly close to the University of Wisconsin Stevens Point campus--me and my friend walked over from campus on Sunday, and I'm sure we haven't been the only ones to walk over

here are some pictures of the cats I took through the window

This was an amazing experience. My wife and I enjoyed a cappuccino and a tea before spending time with the cats. The barista was excellent. The environment was so relaxing and comfortable and the best was yet to come the cat experience was so wonderful absolute stress reliever!

cafes.name: The Pawffee Shop Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 1745 N Casaloma Dr, Appleton, WI 54913, USA

text.text: I visited on a Wednesday, and the cats were so cute and lovable. I went into a room where they kept the cats that had behaved badly, and I saw a really sad-looking cat. I stayed in the room for a while to play with him, hoping it would make him feel a bit happier. I asked the staff lady, and she told me that the reason he was in the room was because he had been harassing the female cats when he was out earlier. I guess it‚Äôs fair that he‚Äôs in the room for some time. The coffee can take some more work but who went there for coffee anyway. Bring me the CATS! I love CAtS.

Only one barista doing his best but there were a lot of customers. The cat play area was pretty clean. We didn't realize that the Cafe itself opened an hour before you could start petting cats. Wish it had been listed more clearly online

From the moment I stepped through the door, I was greeted with genuine warmth and hospitality. The worker up front, Richard, was so knowledgeable and kind and took his time to go through the menu items to help me and my partner find the perfect drink and snack for our visit.

I was thoroughly impressed with the drinks and snacks we chose. The macarons were absolutely delicious and the coffee and tea we ordered were made quickly and had great flavor!

A few aspects of the cafe that stood out to me were the cozy atmosphere as well as impeccable cleanliness and professionalism of the entire establishment. It's clear that the staff goes above and beyond to ensure that both the cats and the patrons have a comfortable and enjoyable experience.

I can't recommend the Pawfee shop enough! Stop by, enjoy some food and drinks, pet some kitties, and maybe even find a new furry family member while you're at it!

cafes.name: BaristaCats Caf√© & Sanctuary for Wayward Cats
cafes.address: 135 W Center St, Whitewater, WI 53190, USA

text.text: Stumbled onto the cafe after hiking locally. As former kitty parents, we fell in love with all 20+ of these little doobers instantly! Great place with a great mission, and all of them were very friendly too.

The cats were adorable, some cuddly and some playful and goofy. The atmosphere was so nice and cozy and the hot cocoa that I had was top tier, the staff was also very nice and introduced us to the backgrounds on some of the cats that they had, we got to meet all kinds of cats and to pet most of them. Will for sure return and hopefully next time adopt one of the fluffballs.

Had a great time hanging out with the cats and kittens at the Caf√©. Everyone was very nice and the atmosphere was very relaxing. Got to pet quite a few new friends and play with a few kittens as well. You can tell they're taking care of the cats very well and they have pride in the space. Definitely will be back again when I can!

cafes.name: Mr. Kitty's Cat Caf√© & Boutique
cafes.address: 502 S Farwell St, Eau Claire, WI 54701, USA

text.text: This is a fantastic place! Cats are cats and will do what they want, but there were plenty out who wanted to play and get attention. Such a great setup for the cats- lots if toys, beds, shelves, and windows and they seem very happy. The boutique side was also wonderful- extremely reasonable prices (I think they could charge more for many of the items!) and a great selection for cat lovers. And remember that any $ you spend is for the humane society, so it's a good cause as well! Great addition to Eau Claire!!!

A cozy cat cafe with friendly staff. A beautiful and quiet place to spend the afternoon. They have a cat lounge and cafe, which are separated from each other. There were at least 7+ cats during my visit.

Absolutely a lovely experience! The cats were very friendly and playful and it was wonderful to sit down and socialize with them. I definitely will be coming back. When you go there definitely dress lightly, they don't have the best ventilation and it gets hot and stuffy in there which didn't mix well with my sweater at all.

cafes.name: The Cat‚Äôs Brew
cafes.address: 2414 Montana Ave, Sun Prairie, WI 53590, USA

text.text:
The Cat's Brew is precisely what the greater Madison area needed. As a self declared cat lady, I'm surprised I didn't hear about this magical place until a few months after it opened. I was struck by how cute the interior of the coffee shop was when I walked in. The staff were super friendly and knowledgeable. The blueberry cream scone I had was very tasty and the folks were kind enough to warm it.

Now. The best part. THE CATS! For $10, I was able to spend an hour with like 10 cats. Most were young, spritely felines. They were all SO sweet. The volunteer gave us the low down on each cat (name, temperament, story if known). We were given toys and treats to give the resident babies. It was truly a dream come true. I can't wait to go back. It is my new favorite coffee shop in the area. Best ever!

‚ö†Ô∏èWARNING ‚ö†Ô∏è You will likely want to adopt one or all the cats. Be advised and prepare accordingly.

A great idea to visit with cats that are up for adoption while sipping on a delicious latte! Great atmosphere, great coffee, and lots of fun kitties to play with! Make sure you reserve ahead to be in the special room with the cats because they book up quickly, especially on the weekends! 5 Stars!!

Beautiful space, great coffee, and cute cats!

They have a full menu of espresso based drinks and smoothies, plus games and reading material in the main cafe area.  Large glass windows allow you to watch the cats even if you aren't in the cat lounge.

The room for the cats is massive with multiple seating areas, cat furniture, and toys.  I went on opening day in the afternoon, so the kitties were pretty well tuckered out from all of the attention.

I look forward to returning once things slow down a bit, but it was great to see a lot of interest today in this new business- especially since it is the only cat cafe in the Madison area.

Our first stop at JC since their move to Lein Rd. Food is every bit as good and service efficient and friendly. Sorry it took us so long. Had the stuffed grilled cheese sandwich and the BOLT sandwich. Both were very good. Nice light supper. Also had the excellent hot cocoa.

Java Cat is a wonderful place!  The coffee is great - always hot and fresh, with a big choice of milk and creamers, and the cold brew is excellent. They have a great selection of teas and other drinks, fresh bakery, a lunch and dinner menu that includes kids options  and delicious gelato. There is plenty of easy parking so it is easy to  pick up takeout or park to eat in.
The service is super friendly and quick and the space is wonderful.  There is lots of uncrowded seating and it‚Äôs a perfect place to read or get some work done on your own, or hold a work meeting or a gathering of friends.  The space is bright and cheerful, full of art and light, and unlike many restaurants the acoustics are very human- friendly.  Even during the busy times you can hear each other talk and also hear yourself think.
There‚Äôs a great children‚Äôs area with cushions and games right in the front dining space and the children of regular customers seem very much at home there.  There‚Äôs a ramp to the front entrance,  the space and bathrooms are accessible, and the staff are happy to shift tables and chairs around.
The outside is a real hidden treasure of a space  with outdoor seating areas, a great breeze, your choice or sun or shade, a peaceful vibe and a visiting family of sandhill cranes.
It is pet friendly with leashed dogs allowed in a portion of the space, and waste bags and water bowls  provided.
I look forward to visiting Java Cat often! üêà‚Äç‚¨õ‚òïÔ∏èüêà‚Äç‚¨õ
A-1... Just possibly use gloves when preparing food otherwise definitely appears super clean  aaaaannnd the food was deeelish... the croissant sandwich is üí•üí•too

I just can‚Äôt stay away too long from the Black Cat üêà‚Äç‚¨õ. It‚Äôs true. There‚Äôs a caring vibe that comes through from the dedicated staff that fills this charming old building with warmth and goodness. The sound of the frother with humming conversations; locally sourced coffee and fresh food ingredients, eclectic artwork from the creative community. Spaces to settle in both outdoors (in season) and in; sometimes live music. And, the Black Cat has this amazing antique display case on the counter, filled with delights from across the street at Ashland Baking Company. My car just naturally pulls onto the Black Cat‚Äôs street by itself. A part of life‚Äôs simple pleasures - do more of what makes you happy.

The coffee here is really good. I got the Myan mocha and it was fantastic. The coffee had a different body and didnt rely on sugar to make it taste good.

The quiche was excellent as well.

Definitely a nice place to stop at when up in Ashland.

Love this place for a morning or afternoon stop, or both in the same day when I‚Äôm in Ashland! My almond milk maple hot latte was fabulous this morning, omelette and veggie hash. Black Cat Salad and Sandeich with my cold brew also fabulous this afternoon. I love getting my fill here! Yum!

cafes.name: Alley Cat Coffeehouse
cafes.address: 213 W Main St, Hortonville, WI 54944, USA

text.text: The horchata latte was phenomenal. The staff caters to your coffee wants and desires. They also have an awesome cat logo and are a local business! Let‚Äôs fight to keep places like this open. Small businesses like this are what makeüóΩ America üá∫üá∏ so great! An overall wonderful and ‚Äútasty‚Äù experience coming here.
Always lovely service. The food, the drinks, the atmosphere, all top notch. If you read books and enjoy the cozy, small town coffee shop vibe ..this is it.

My first time stopping here the atmosphere was super peaceful. I loved my latte. The decor was beautiful and the note about her friends passing broke me. It‚Äôs beautiful to see she made something out of the tragedy that took place with her friend and donates to the local High School.

Roselle.name: The Cat House
Roselle.address: 344 Irving Park Rd, Roselle, IL 60172, USA

text.text: Visiting the new Cat House is a must if you‚Äôre a cat lover in the suburbs. It‚Äôs a lot of fun and you definitely won‚Äôt be bored when you‚Äôre here, plenty of kitties walking around, playing or sleeping. There‚Äôs also educational materials, books, and games and you can also purchase cat-themed merchandise. A lot of photo opportunities! The place is clean and doesn‚Äôt have an odor. I would definitely come back again soon.

This place is amazing. I wanted to adopt all the cats. The staff is wonderful. It is very clean. And talk about therapeutic getting to spend 45 minutes with the fur babies. It's a fantastic experience!!

Update: I adopted my first kitten from here!!! Amazing experience, staff was very kind and we managed to get everything done the same day since I already applied for a different cat a week prior. Her name at the house was Noah, a little midnight sweetheart, we now renamed her to Koi. Thank you again heartland and cat house!

Amazing experience that is a higher quality than the cafes in Chicago. No screaming kids harassing cats and very relaxing atmosphere and experience. Staff was attentive and very experienced. Thank you for the great time!

cafes.name: Fat Cat Coffee Works
cafes.address: 606 Railroad St, New Glarus, WI 53574, USA

text.text: Finally stopped in to check this place out and can‚Äôt believe how disappointing the food was.  Menu online described your typical avocado toast with an egg on top.  Instead I got avocado toast with no egg and tomato/olives/feta on.  Mediterranean avocado toast simply does not taste good nor was i expecting it.  To add on, my girlfriend‚Äôs sausage/egg burrito had cinnamon which also has no place in a breakfast burrito.  The only saving grace was the amazing coffee and neat atmosphere.

Everything was super good! We had mango and strawberry smoothies, avocado toast, the harvest benedict and a cherry pie. All super delicious! The service was excellent as well. People are super friendly and nice. We will be coming back!
Really great people and vibe. Plenty of indoor and outdoor seating. Great food and drinks, savory or sweet. I had chili with hash browns and eggs on top. Excellent üëç
